public class NEATSurvivalFilterImpl
extends AbstractNEATSurvivalFilter

An implementation of NEATSurvivalFilter, where it marks dead NEATGenomes and species in a NEATPopulation with a GeneMap type data.

When marking genomes, all but the fittest genomes (the number as derived from NEATEvolutionFieldMap.eliteProportion()) in each species are marked. When marking species, stagnant species (those who haven't experience fitness improvement after NEATEvolutionFieldMap.speciesDropoffAge() generations) and terminally unfit species (those whom fitness sharing causes to have a 0 target size) are marked, excepting the species that contains the populations most fit genome.

NEATSurvivalFilterImpl instances will not remove genomes, leaving them for removal at the discretion of the EvolutionStrategy.

Author:
Luis Guimbarda
